args:
With Audric's help, the prince manages to lay
Chronos low, meaning the time for the two
men to part is at hand. Feeling a sense of
familiarity at Audric's harsh—but warm—gaze,
the prince vows that he will move toward a
future shaped by his own actions alone.
I am infinite! Time has no end!
Not this time, Chronos! I will reclaim\nthe half of me from you!
By the pact sworn, come to me, Zodiark!
That voice is coming from INSIDE Chronos!
I would have you remember that your\nbody is something borrowed!
And I will have it returned to me,\nalong with my pride!
There's a dragon coming out\nof Chronos's body!\nBut...that isn't the Zodiark I know!
Though his form may appear different,\nthat is indeed one of the Six Greatwyrms:\nthe Shadowwyrm Zodiark.
Chronos is an amalgamation created by\nfusing the Six Greatwyrms into one being.
I had no idea that was even possible!
It is for the Dyrenell Empire of this time.
And it is this great power which granted\nhim the ability to alter time itself.
So by removing Zodiark, Chronos will\nno longer be able to manipulate time?
You speak folly! I have lost no more\nthan a mere fragment of myself!
And yet, the loss of even that one\nfragment means you can no longer\nfollow along the chain of causality.
Thank you, Audric. This was only\npossible because of you.
If you hadn't helped, I would've been left\nto drown in a sea of my own regrets.
Perhaps—and yet, it was you who chose\nto stand up and move forward once more.\nYou should be proud of that.
Me? Yeah, I'm good. But, ummm...
And I'm sorry I said all those terrible\nthings to you.
It's all right, Notte. I know you had\nreasons for thinking what you did.
I can only imagine what kind of\nunspeakable things happened here.
Do you wish to know about the future?
Before long, you will be drawn back to\nyour own time by the chain of causality.
As I will be unable to follow you there,\nthis is the final aid I can offer.
If you wish it, I can tell you what\nbecomes of you in the future.
But if I were to gain that knowledge,\nI would become trapped by it.
It would feel like my future would no\nlonger be mine. So by not knowing it,\nI can shape it however I want.
I want to walk toward my future on my own\nfeet and grasp it in my own hands.
So thank you, but I'll pass.
The time of our parting has come.
With Chronos defeated, we will never see\neach other again.
But I feel like you have so much\nmore to teach me...
At first, I had wished to avoid you.

This world is so much crueler than
imagined, so I swore to bring about a
new world of peace no matter what fate
this action would burden me with.
And yet, I feel that resolve weakened\nwhen I look upon your face now...
Oh, it isn't your fault. In fact, your desire\nto forge your own future is naught but\na sign of great strength.
Perhaps this world of despair contains\na flicker of hope after all.
Farewell, {player_name}.\nI pray you are able to overcome your fate.
Cassandra said that other worlds are\nones of alternate possibilities.
And Audric had a pact with Zodiark.
Plus, that familiar look in his eyes...
Ah! I think I know who Audric is!
